					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10630764#post-4184046</guid>
				<title>Author Post</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-10630764/clash-of-the-cosmic-comedians#post-4184046</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 14 Mar 2019 06:19:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TyGently</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2038009</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a trilogy. All three parts are entries in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/144-hour-jam-contest">144 Hour Jam Contest</a>. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5mxXSvaBWRI">God have mercy on my soul.</a></p> <p><strong>1. <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4844">SCP-4844 - Last Man Standing</a></strong><br /> <strong>2. <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/what-s-the-deal">What's The Deal?</a></strong><br /> <strong>3. Clash of the Cosmic Comedians</strong> (you are here)</p> <p>Who says I can't <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/what-happened-at-greenwich">finish</a> a <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/comedown-machine-hub">tale series</a>?</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Show&nbsp;Commentary</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide&nbsp;Commentary</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>With the completion of <em>What's The Deal?</em>, I was committed to slaying this thing. And slay it I did.</p> <p>I'm actually pretty satisfied with how this whole thing turned out. Despite being produced on such a short timescale and under three different themes, it feels more cohesive than I thought it would be when planning it. This was a fun experience.</p> <p>To address the elephant in the room: I don't like Tim Allen at all. He is a stale, repetitive, and bigoted man who engages almost entirely in punching down while he constantly plays himself as the victim. The only worthwhile thing he has produced in his life is the Toy Story series (and maybe The Santa Clause, but that's debatable), and he is barely responsible at all for its success.</p> <p>Jerry Seinfeld does have some of the same problems, but he has a much greater capacity for change and self-awareness. Not to mention, he's just plain funny. Much of modern comedy and modern television owes a great deal to him, and his work is a guilty pleasure of mine.</p> <p>Thanks to everyone who took a look at this before posting.</p> </div> </div> </div> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
